  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
        <div xml:id="KT59-kilavi">
          <p type="edition">piriviṭai aḻinta kiḻattiyait tōḻi vaṟpuṟuttiyatu.</p>
          <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">The confidante encouraging HER who was desolate in the time of separation.</p>
          </div>



        <div xml:id="KT59">
            <lg type="edition">
<l>                patalaip pāṇip paricilar kōmāṉ</l>
<l>                ṟalaikkuṉṟat takalvāyk kuṇṭucuṉaik kuvaḷaiyoṭu</l>
<l>                potinta kuḷavi nāṟuniṉ ṉaṟunuta</l>
<l>                ṟāveṉa maṟapparō maṟṟē muyalavuñ</l>
<l>                curampala vilaṅkiya varumporu </l>
<l>                ṇirampā vākali ṉīṭalō viṉṟē.</l>
             </lg>
            <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
             <l>
                <choice>
                    <seg>Will he forget in a rush</seg>
                    <seg>will he ever forget ...?</seg>
                </choice>
             </l>
             <l rend="indent">your fragrant forehead, smelling of wild jasmine tied</l>
             <l rend="indent2">with waterlilies from the deep broad-mouthed pool on the hill top</l>
             <l rend="indent">[belonging to] the king of
                <choice>
                    <seg>suppliants</seg>
                    <seg>solicitors</seg>
                </choice>
                with the beat of drums?<note place="foot">Solicitors with drums presumably are the traveling minstrels for whom the king is always at home. If HE is the subject also of line 1 (1+4b), this might be considered as an elliptical metaphor about his generosity.</note>
             </l>
             <l rend="indent">Because, even if he makes an effort,</l>
             <l rend="indent">the wealth difficult [to attain] lying athwart in many deserts</l>
             <l rend="indent">has not been attained,</l>
             <l rend="indent4">will there be delay?<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">nīṭalō</term>: the <term xml:lang="ta">-ō</term> here is one of the difficult cases. It seems possible to understand an actual question which is negated immediately afterwards (<term xml:lang="ta">iṉṟē</term>). Possible as well is a demarcation of topic.</note> No.</l>


             
                </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
